@CreoleResource(name="StanfordParser",
                comment="Stanford parser wrapper",
                helpURL="http://gate.ac.uk/userguide/sec:parsers:stanford")
public class Parser
extends gate.creole.AbstractLanguageAnalyser
implements gate.ProcessingResource

GATE PR wrapper around the Stanford Parser. This class expects to find Token and Sentence annotations (such as those created by the ANNIE tokenizer and splitter) already in the inputAS and transforms them into suitable data structures, which it feeds to the LexicalizedParser. The parser's output can be stored in the outputAS in various ways, controlled by CREOLE run-time parameters.

Author:
adam

tlppClass

protected String tlppClass
The TreebankLangParserParams implementation to use. This is where we get the language pack, and then the GrammaticalStructureFactory used to extract the dependencies from the parse. In most cases you should leave this at the default value, which is suitable for English text.

dependenciesFeature

protected String dependenciesFeature
The name of the feature to add to tokens. The feature value is a List of DependencyRelation objects giving the dependencies from this token to other tokens.

annotatePhraseStructureRecursively

protected gate.Annotation annotatePhraseStructureRecursively(edu.stanford.nlp.trees.Tree tree,
                                                             edu.stanford.nlp.trees.Tree rootTree)
Generate a SyntaxTreeNode Annotation corresponding to this Tree. Work recursively so that the annotations are actually generated from the bottom up, in order to build the consists list of annotation IDs.

Parameters:
tree - the current subtree
rootTree - the whole sentence, used to find the span of the current subtree
Returns:
a GATE Annotation of type "SyntaxTreeNode"
